name: v2.0.0.M8

name: v2.0.0.M5
body:
With this release we fixed a couple of bugs (one introduced in 2.0.0.M4) and we improved the split by size task to be more accurate in case of optimization.
Here the [full list](https://github.com/torakiki/sejda/issues?q=milestone%3A2.0.0.M5+is%3Aclosed).

name: v2.0.0.M4
body:
New milestone release where we added:
- Attachments collection task to combine PDFs into a PDF portfolio
- AddBackPages task that takes one or more pages form a PDF document and adds them to one or more PDF documents after each 'n' pages
- Added many possible optimizations to the compress task, made it faster and a little less eager on memory
- Added a --optimize parameter to the split and extract tasks making Sejda try to remove unused resources from the generated PDF documents, making them smaller

name: v2.0.0.M1
body:
First milestone for the Sejda 2. We changed Sejda into a layer over [SAMBox](https://github.com/torakiki/sambox) for which we have full control so we don't depend on third party libraries. We dropped support for iText and PDFBox implementations even though Sejda architecture still allows tasks to be implemented using any PDF engine. 
Sejda-console tasks are now entirely based on SAMBox except for a couple if ICEpdf based. We fixed some bugs, added some option to existing tasks and added some new task:
- Combine and reorder
- Compress
- Extract by bookmarks
- Split by content change
- Split down the middle

name: v1.0.0.RELEASE
body: Renamed some classes to use the word "Outline" instead of "Bookmarks". Minor bug fixes in the console.

name: v1.0.0.M10
body:
PdfToJpeg now accepts a page range. Also now works with OpenJDK.
Compiled artifacts include debug information.
PdfBox and IcePDF were upgraded to their latest version.
CLI supports Split by every X pages task.
_BREAKING CHANGE_: Split by pages will now split _after_ the given pages. (see https://github.com/torakiki/sejda/issues/153)

name: v1.0.0.M9
body: Upgraded some dependencies, simplified some internal logic and moved conversion logic to its own module. Enhanced prefix functionality with some simple arithmetic and the Merge task directory input with a regex option. ExtractTextByPages now bursts text to a text file per page. Created a .deb archive for Debian based linux distributions.

name: v1.0.0.M8
body: New task released: ExtractTextByPages: extracts text from a pdf document, splitting output text files by pages

Some bug was fixed (pdf compression and merge of the outline of the pdf documents). 
When merging pdf documents you can now choose to merge the outline (bookmarks), discard it or create a new one with one entry for each document you are merging.

A new parameter to set userzoom factor has been added to the tasks converting pdf documents to images (Pdf To Tiff, Pdf To Jpg). With this new parameter you can define the desired zoom factor (Ex. 150%) of the generated images, this will result in higher resolution and in the end better images. Other minor issues have been added/changed
